    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> divina
                        favente clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Decet nostram pietatem
                        predecessorum nostrorum tramites sequi et maxime ecclesiarum utilitates
                        reformare, quatenus eos mereamur habere apud Dominum intercessores, qui in
                        presenti seculo nos cognoscunt suae Ecclesiae adiutores. Quapropter omnium
                        fidelium sanctae Dei Ecclesiae nostrorumque presentium scilicet et futurorum
                        noverit sollertia, <persName key="#Intercessory #Bishops #fidelisOf"
                            ref="#people/215">Amolonem</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/8">Taurinensem</placeName> venerabilem <rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcopum</rs> ac <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Palatine_count #fidelisOf" ref="#people/57"
                            >Sigefredum</persName> illustrem <rs key="#Count">comitem</rs>
                        dilectissimos <rs key="#fidelisOf">fideles nostros</rs> suggessisse nostrae
                        serenitati, quatenus pro divino intuitu <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >duas curtes</rs> quae vocantur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#estates/159">Saluciola</geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#estates/35">Evoriano</geogName> cum omnibus pertinentiis et
                        adiacentiis seu <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            >familiis suis</rs> prisco tempore pertinentes de <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/161">comitatu Parmensi</geogName>, quas
                        quondam <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/32">Karolus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> consuprinus predecessor noster
                            <orgName
                            key="#Natural_landscape #Rivers #Mountains #Curtes #Mansi #Landed_possessions #Forests #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Hay/fodder #Churches #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/34">ecclesiae Beati Nicomedis</orgName> quae est
                        in <placeName ref="#places/29">Fontana Broculi</placeName> per sua precepta
                        donavit, nostra preceptali auctoritate predicto sancto loco confirmaremus.
                        Quorum precibus libenti animo annuentes decrevimus ita fieri. Confirmamus
                        igitur eidem Sancti Nicomedis ecclesiae prefatas curtes cum omnibus
                        pertinentiis et adiacentiis suis in integrum, <rs
                            key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >mansis videlicet vestitis atque absentibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terris</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Wine #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Cereals #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >campis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >pratis</rs>, <rs>pascuis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >silvis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Natural_landscape #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >vallibus, planiciebus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fruits/vegetables #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >arboribus pomiferis et infructuosis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs> seu <rs
                            key="#Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >molendinis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >capella</rs> quoque in ipsa terra constructa, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            >familiis etiam utriusque sexus servis, ancillis</rs>, et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Aldius"
                            >aldionibus</rs>, omnia omnino cum iudiciariis quaecumque dici vel
                        nominari possunt, quae iuste et legaliter ad ipsas curtes pertinere
                        noscuntur. Precipientes iubemus ut <rs key="#Immunity">nullus iudiciariae
                            potestatis dux, marchio, comes, vicecomes, sculdassius, locopositus aut
                            quislibet rei publicae procurator, neque aliqua persona uniuscuiusque
                            ordinis aut dignitatis parva vel magna ex eisdem rebus quoquo modo se
                            intromittere aut devestire presumat sine legali iudicio</rs>, sed liceat
                        rectori predicti sancti loci ad partem ipsius ecclesiae omnes easdem res <rs
                            key="#Natural_landscape #Rivers #Curtes #Mansi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Forests #Mills #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                            >iure proprietario</rs> perpetuis temporibus possidere, et quod rectius
                        previderint ad eiusdem sancti loci utilitatem peragere, remota totius
                        potestatis inquietudine. Si quis autem, quod minime credimus, contra hoc
                        nostrae pietatis et confirmationis preceptum quandoque insurgere
                        temptaverit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras
                            XXX</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem palatio nostro</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem parti ipsius
                            ecclesiae</rs>. Et ut ab omnibus verius credatur et diligentius
                        observetur, mano propria roboratum anuli nostri impressione subter iussimus
                        sigillari. Signum domni Berengarii gloriosissimi regis. <persName
                            key="#Notary"><name ref="Martianus">Martianus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/58">Petri</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. Data VIII id. mart.,
                        anno incarnationis Domini DCCCXCVIIII, domni autem Berengarii gloriosissimi
                        regis XIII, indictione II. Actum <placeName ref="#places/65"
                            >Papie</placeName>. In Dei nomine feliciter, amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
